# Load the DataFrame from the CSV file
data = pd.read_csv("D:/Gry fabularne/Studia 2/Semestr 2/Projekt Bolan/Dobry/xxx.csv")
data_2 = pd.read_csv("D:/Gry fabularne/Studia 2/Semestr 2/Projekt Bolan/Dobry/yyy.csv",sep=';')

# Combine 'YEAR', 'MO', and 'DY' columns into a single 'Data' column
data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data[['YEAR', 'MO', 'DY']].astype(str).agg('-'.join, axis=1))

# Now 'Data' column contains the combined date from 'YEAR', 'MO', and 'DY' columns
# You can drop the original 'YEAR', 'MO', and 'DY' columns if needed
data.drop(['YEAR', 'MO', 'DY'], axis=1, inplace=True)

#changing the name of a column
data.rename(columns={'T2M': 't'}, inplace=True)

#################

#New column to crate avg temperature
data_2['t'] = (data_2['tmin'] + data_2['tmax']) / 2
#Dropping unneeded columns
data_2.drop(['lat', 'long', 'elev', 'tmin', 'tmax'], axis=1, inplace=True)

data_2.rename(columns={'date': 'Date'}, inplace=True)

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error
from math import sqrt
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Przykadowe dane
# Zakadam, e df_nasa_1_train i df_nasa_1_test to ramki danych zawierajce dane treningowe i testowe odpowiednio
# Zmienne df_nasa_1_train i df_nasa_1_test powinny by zdefiniowane wczeniej

# Dopasowanie modelu ARIMA
model = ARIMA(df_nasa_1_train, order=(3, 0, 3))
model_fit = model.fit()

# Prognozowanie
forecast = model_fit.forecast(steps=len(df_nasa_1_test))[0]

# Wizualizacja prognoz i danych testowych
plt.plot(forecast, label='Forecast', color='blue')
plt.plot(df_nasa_1_test, label='Actual', color='red')
plt.xlabel('Time')
plt.ylabel('Value')
plt.title('ARIMA Model Forecast vs Actual')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Obliczenie RMSE
rmse = sqrt(mean_squared_error(df_nasa_1_test, forecast))
print("RMSE:", rmse)

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error
from math import sqrt
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Przykadowe dane
# Zakadam, e df_nasa_1_train i df_nasa_1_test to ramki danych zawierajce dane treningowe i testowe odpowiednio
# Zmienne df_nasa_1_train i df_nasa_1_test powinny by zdefiniowane wczeniej

# Dopasowanie modelu ARIMA
model = ARIMA(df_nasa_1_train, order=(3, 0, 3))
model_fit = model.fit()

# Prognozowanie
forecast = model_fit.forecast(steps=len(df_nasa_1_test))

# Wizualizacja prognoz i danych testowych
plt.plot(forecast, label='Forecast', color='blue')
plt.plot(df_nasa_1_test.values, label='Actual', color='red')  # Przeksztacamy DataFrame na tablic numpy
plt.xlabel('Time')
plt.ylabel('Value')
plt.title('ARIMA Model Forecast vs Actual')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Obliczenie RMSE
rmse = sqrt(mean_squared_error(df_nasa_1_test.values, forecast))
print("RMSE:", rmse)
